      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Religious groups absolutely have the right to opt out of government mandates that directly conflict with their core beliefs, as this is a fundamental protection of religious freedom. Allowing such exemptions strengthens the principle of a secular state by ensuring the government does not impose its values on individuals, rather than undermining it. If we force religious organizations to violate their conscience, we erode trust in both the faith community and the government itself. Ultimately, a healthy society requires balancing state authority with the deep, personal convictions of its citizens.",
      "source": "target",
